Actor Gideon Okeke has called out popular movie maker, Frank Rajah, over alleged N500,000 debt. Okeke, in an Instagram post, alleged Rajah has failed to pay the debt after over three years. Describing the filmmaker as one of the ‘horrible bosses in Nollywood’, the Tinsel star said Frank’s action would never be if there were structures in Nollywood “The filmmaker, Frank Rajah owes me 500k! I’ve been quiet for 3 years now. Some very important and influential people know this. But like Frank says: “Dem go beat me ni?”, the actor wrote.   Filmmaker Moses Ebere dies     Cuppy reacts after Twitter user tells her to get pregnant     Toyin Abraham, Mercy Aigbe, others solicits fund for ailing…   “If there were structures, this kneegar wouldn’t dare bully himself or try to outsmart me of my ‘SWEAT EQUITY’. You’ve heard of horrible bosses in Nollywood yea? This kneegar one.” He also urged the public to alert him and ensure they drag Rajah when they happen on the movie at any point as he disclosed its title. “The film is titled: The BAG MAN. In the event of a title change, if you see my face ANYWHERE in a film by him, abeg shout FOUL PLAY FOR ME!”